Flow:
HTTP request → Controller (@RestController) → Service (@Service) → Repository (JpaRepository) → Database

Postman (HTTP request)
  → Controller (@RestController) — receives request, calls service
  → Service (@Service) — business logic, calls repository
  → Repository (JpaRepository interface) — Spring auto-generates SQL
  → Hibernate — translates to actual SQL
  → H2 Database — stores/retrieves rows


Controller->Maps which http request goes to which service
Service-> does findAll, save kinds of operations
Repository-> interface(not class) which extends JpaRepository<the entity this repository manages, type of entity's @Id field>

Model: outline of Database, has entities @Entity, has getter and setters and constructor as fields are defined here.
@Entity: Marks a class as a DB table

super(): Calls parent constructor from subclass

the foreign key always lives on the "many" side